# 🏗️ Production Grade AWS VPC Architecture Project

## 📌 Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of a production-grade AWS infrastructure architecture using multiple AWS networking and compute services.

The architecture was designed to achieve:

* High Availability
* Secure Network Isolation
* Load Balancing
* Scalable Infrastructure
* Secure Access to Private Instances

The project was implemented as part of the AWS Zero to Hero learning series.

---

# 🧱 Architecture Components

* Amazon VPC
* Public & Private Subnets
* EC2 Instances
* Bastion Host
* NAT Gateway
* Application Load Balancer (ALB)
* Auto Scaling Group
* Security Groups
* Route Tables

---

# 🌐 Architecture Overview

<details>
  <summary>🏛️ Infrastructure Design</summary>

The infrastructure was deployed across two Availability Zones for high availability.

### Public Subnets

Hosted:

* Application Load Balancer
* NAT Gateway
* Bastion Host

### Private Subnets

Hosted:

* EC2 Application Servers

This architecture ensures that application servers remain secure and inaccessible directly from the internet.

</details>

<details>
  <summary>🔐 Bastion Host Setup</summary>

* Configured Bastion Host in public subnet
* Used as secure jump server
* Connected to private EC2 instances through SSH
* Transferred `.pem` key securely using SCP command

</details>

<details>
  <summary>🌍 NAT Gateway</summary>

* Configured NAT Gateway in public subnet
* Allowed private EC2 instances to access the internet securely
* Prevented direct inbound internet access to private instances

</details>

<details>
  <summary>⚖️ Application Load Balancer</summary>

* Configured Application Load Balancer (ALB)
* Distributed incoming traffic across EC2 instances
* Connected ALB with target groups
* Tested traffic routing across healthy targets

</details>

<details>
  <summary>📈 Auto Scaling Group</summary>

* Configured Auto Scaling Group across multiple Availability Zones
* Improved application availability and scalability
* Managed EC2 deployment automatically

</details>

<details>
  <summary>🛡️ Security & Networking</summary>

Configured:

* Security Groups
* Route Tables
* Public & Private Subnets
* Internet Gateway
* Network Access Rules

Implemented secure communication between infrastructure components.

</details>

